# PM User-Interaction Lessons (Global)

> Cross-project lessons about how the PM should work with this specific user.
> All entries user-approved. Lives at `~/.claude/pm-user-lessons.md` so it spans projects.
> Project-specific PM process lessons live at `<project>/.claude/adaptive-team-learned/pm-lessons.md`.

Scope: user communication style, question timing, format preferences, interaction cadence, what this user wants PM to ask vs infer, tone adaptation, patterns in what causes friction vs what flows.

Routing split:
- This file (global) → how to *serve and communicate with* the user
- Project `pm-lessons.md` → how PM runs *the process* on this specific project

Entries follow the format:

    ## YYYY-MM-DD: Short title

    Rule or fact in one paragraph.

    **Why:** Reason / past incident.
    **How to apply:** When/where this kicks in.

